data.description: Flow, architecture & design quality make this spectacular post and beam waterfront home a rare find indeed!  This 3 bedroom, 2 bath Acorn Deck style home is nestled in a private, wooded setting on Pierce Creek which has deep-water access to the Neuse River & ICW just a few minutes away!  This home is In the Village of Oriental only a short distance away from shopping, banking & fine dining from the many available eateries!  Built on a double-lot of 1.05 acres with over 212 feet of waterfrontage that features a new boat dock with 5 feet of controlling water depth and two docking areas of 30 feet & 22 feet that are facing SW and are perfectly protected from storms!  Floor to ceiling casement windows allow ambient lighting to flow throughout and dimensional vaulted T & G wood ceilings accent this spacious open floor plan!  A private spacious deck accessible from the master bedroom, dining & kitchen areas offers waterfront vistas & cool prevailing summer breezes below the natural canopy of mature oaks, elms & maples!  Enjoy the cozy fireplace on wintery nights.  Comes with a spacious studio for the artist and/or craftsman alike!  No HOA or HOA dues!  Community boat ramp & tennis court!  Oriental is the Sailing Capital of North Carolina and offers world-class saltwater fishing year round!  Nothin' could be Finer!
